WEBVTT

1
00:00:36.870 --> 00:00:38.080
I'm hungry.

2
00:00:38.163 --> 00:00:40.540
A lady
never complains.


3
00:00:40.624 --> 00:00:42.417
We can't
eat dresses.


4
00:00:43.710 --> 00:00:46.463
If only the Duke
had sent bread.


5
00:00:46.546 --> 00:00:48.298
I think he wants
to marry you.


6
00:00:48.382 --> 00:00:50.008
I'd rather
marry you.


7
00:00:50.092 --> 00:00:51.677
He's a Duke.

8
00:00:51.760 --> 00:00:55.430
And you, my dear,
a rapidly ageing orphan.


9
00:00:55.514 --> 00:00:57.182
Ah, Marie!

10
00:00:57.266 --> 00:01:00.018
Well, I won't be rescued.
I'm not in distress.


11
00:01:00.102 --> 00:01:02.479
We have no money.
Not a bean.


12
00:01:02.562 --> 00:01:04.564
Your whole life,
our country has been at war...


13
00:01:04.648 --> 00:01:05.983
and everyone must make...
Everyone must make...


14
00:01:07.442 --> 00:01:09.820
I don't love
the Duke de Guiche.


15
00:01:09.903 --> 00:01:11.113
Wear the dress
he sent.


16
00:01:11.196 --> 00:01:14.825
No. Red is vulgar,
and it reeks of lechery.


17
00:01:14.908 --> 00:01:15.993
Have you seen my shoes?

18
00:01:16.076 --> 00:01:17.661
If you don't love him...
Or even like him.


19
00:01:17.744 --> 00:01:20.497
Why did you accept his
invitation to the theater?


20
00:01:20.580 --> 00:01:24.543
Because we can't afford the
tickets, and I want to see the play.


21
00:01:26.753 --> 00:01:28.463
He's here.

22
00:01:29.047 --> 00:01:30.924
He's here.

23
00:01:31.008 --> 00:01:32.718
He's here.
Now, don't be rude to him.


24
00:01:32.801 --> 00:01:34.052
I'm not rude.

25
00:01:34.136 --> 00:01:37.055
I am enigmatically distant
and fashionably late.


26
00:01:37.139 --> 00:01:38.223
Where are my shoes?

27
00:01:38.307 --> 00:01:40.225
If you anger him,
he'll ruin us.


28
00:01:40.309 --> 00:01:42.144
Marry the Duke
and you'll be rich.


29
00:01:42.227 --> 00:01:44.062
A clever marriage
is your only option.


30
00:01:44.146 --> 00:01:46.023
I have no intention
of marrying anyone.


31
00:01:46.106 --> 00:01:48.692
Believe me,
spinsterhood is bleak.


32
00:01:48.775 --> 00:01:51.236
And love,
does that mean nothing to you?


33
00:01:51.320 --> 00:01:55.741
It might smell rosy for a year
or two, but love doesn't last.


34
00:01:55.824 --> 00:02:00.120
What lasts is compromise
and sacrifice.


35
00:02:00.954 --> 00:02:02.080
Children need love.

36
00:02:02.164 --> 00:02:03.498
Adults need money.

37
00:02:08.253 --> 00:02:09.254
Hello, Jacques.

38
00:02:09.338 --> 00:02:10.839
Marie. Marie.

39
00:02:10.922 --> 00:02:12.341
Tell your mistress she's two
months behind with the rent.


40
00:02:12.424 --> 00:02:13.717
It's coming, I promise.

41
00:02:13.800 --> 00:02:15.177
Two months!

42
00:02:16.678 --> 00:02:18.263
Marie!

43
00:02:21.975 --> 00:02:23.185
It's perfectly fetching.

44
00:02:23.268 --> 00:02:25.979
I just long to see you
in crimson silk.


45
00:02:26.063 --> 00:02:27.940
-I couldn't wear that dress.
-Oh?


46
00:02:28.023 --> 00:02:30.108
I don't have
the shoes to match. Sorry.


47
00:02:30.192 --> 00:02:33.070
Oh, I'll rectify
your errant shoelessness.


48
00:02:33.153 --> 00:02:36.365
Maybe the good Duke should've
send you the dress, Valvert.


49
00:02:36.448 --> 00:02:38.450
Oh, no, I tried it.

50
00:02:38.533 --> 00:02:40.535
It was too loose
on the bust.


51
00:02:41.995 --> 00:02:44.456
At least you have
more than one pair of shoes.


52
00:02:44.539 --> 00:02:47.626
<i>What does it feel like</i>

53
00:02:47.709 --> 00:02:50.712
<i>To slow dance in sunlight</i>

54
00:02:50.796 --> 00:02:54.716
<i>With someone you love?</i>

55
00:02:56.301 --> 00:02:59.554
<i>Somebody who sees you</i>

56
00:02:59.638 --> 00:03:02.557
<i>And won't ever leave you</i>

57
00:03:02.641 --> 00:03:08.397
<i>Alone</i>
<i>Whatever comes</i>


58
00:03:08.480 --> 00:03:11.233
<i>I need something</i>
<i>to die for</i>


59
00:03:11.316 --> 00:03:14.486
<i>Write poems and cry for</i>

60
00:03:14.569 --> 00:03:18.407
<i>And I won't be ashamed</i>

61
00:03:20.575 --> 00:03:23.245
<i>I'm nobody's pet</i>

62
00:03:23.328 --> 00:03:26.873
<i>No one's wife</i>
<i>no one's woman</i>


63
00:03:27.916 --> 00:03:30.419
<i>And I won't play that game</i>

64
00:03:30.502 --> 00:03:36.341
<i>I'd give anything</i>
<i>for someone to say</i>


65
00:03:36.425 --> 00:03:39.886
<i>That they can't live</i>
<i>without me</i>


66
00:03:39.970 --> 00:03:42.222
<i>And they'll be there forever</i>

67
00:03:42.306 --> 00:03:48.353
<i>I'd give anything</i>
<i>for someone to say to me</i>


68
00:03:48.437 --> 00:03:52.190
<i>That no matter</i>
<i>how bad it gets</i>


69
00:03:52.274 --> 00:03:56.445
<i>They won't turn away from me</i>

70
00:03:58.447 --> 00:04:00.907
<i>What do you do</i>

71
00:04:00.991 --> 00:04:04.036
<i>When you're</i>
<i>always waiting</i>


72
00:04:04.119 --> 00:04:07.623
<i>To find love</i>
<i>at first sight?</i>


73
00:04:10.459 --> 00:04:13.462
<i>If I'm naive</i>

74
00:04:13.545 --> 00:04:17.174
<i>Why does all the poetry</i>

75
00:04:18.008 --> 00:04:20.427
<i>Say that I might?</i>

76
00:04:22.471 --> 00:04:25.182
<i>I have heard</i>
<i>songs that say</i>


77
00:04:25.265 --> 00:04:28.268
<i>Love conquers everything</i>

78
00:04:28.352 --> 00:04:31.438
<i>However you name it</i>

79
00:04:34.274 --> 00:04:37.027
<i>It's right there</i>
<i>in front of you</i>


80
00:04:37.110 --> 00:04:40.238
<i>Wherever you are</i>

81
00:04:40.322 --> 00:04:43.116
<i>You just have to claim it</i>
<i>Claim it</i>


82
00:05:00.759 --> 00:05:01.843
Who's that?

83
00:05:01.927 --> 00:05:03.011
The Duke de Guiche.

84
00:05:03.095 --> 00:05:04.596
Second only
to the King.


85
00:05:04.680 --> 00:05:05.764
No, the lady.

86
00:05:05.847 --> 00:05:07.849
Oh, Roxanne.

87
00:05:07.933 --> 00:05:10.143
Well above your station,
my friend.


88
00:05:14.523 --> 00:05:16.900
Oh, what superb ribbons,
Duke de Guiche.


89
00:05:16.984 --> 00:05:19.236
Gorgeous piping.
And trim.


90
00:05:19.319 --> 00:05:20.696
Doeskin and
beaver, ladies.


91
00:05:20.779 --> 00:05:22.114
Doeskin and beaver.

92
00:05:25.534 --> 00:05:26.618
Yes, thank you.

93
00:05:26.702 --> 00:05:27.703
Stop there, sir.

94
00:05:30.414 --> 00:05:31.415
In you go, sir.

95
00:05:41.008 --> 00:05:42.050
...sir.

96
00:05:48.515 --> 00:05:50.642
Be swift,
be crafty...


97
00:05:50.726 --> 00:05:52.894
take from the women
and the men without swords.


98
00:05:52.978 --> 00:05:53.979
And children?

99
00:05:55.397 --> 00:05:57.566
A child
with a full purse is an adult.


100
00:05:57.649 --> 00:06:01.278
- <i>I'd give anything for</i>
-<i>someone to say</i>


101
00:06:01.361 --> 00:06:03.196
<i>For someone to say</i>

102
00:06:03.280 --> 00:06:06.742
<i>That they can't live</i>
<i>without me</i>


103
00:06:06.825 --> 00:06:09.286
<i>And they'll be there forever</i>

104
00:06:09.369 --> 00:06:15.125
<i>I'd give anything</i>
<i>for someone to say to me</i>


105
00:06:15.208 --> 00:06:18.920
-<i>That no matter That no matter</i>
-<i>how bad it gets</i>


106
00:06:19.004 --> 00:06:22.633
<i>They won't</i>
<i>turn away from me</i>


107
00:06:24.927 --> 00:06:30.515
- <i>If love's there,
I'll feel</i> -<i>it and its stare</i>


108
00:06:30.599 --> 00:06:33.936
<i>It'll be freedom</i>
<i>at first sight</i>


109
00:06:34.019 --> 00:06:37.147
<i>I'll be walking on air</i>

110
00:06:37.230 --> 00:06:41.944
<i>If love's there</i>
<i>won't dare run away</i>


111
00:06:42.778 --> 00:06:46.448
<i>I'll swallow my pride</i>

112
00:06:47.115 --> 00:06:49.409
<i>And I'll ask</i>

113
00:06:51.119 --> 00:06:54.957
<i>You to stay</i>

114
00:07:14.977 --> 00:07:15.978
Thief!

115
00:07:18.230 --> 00:07:19.231
Hey!

116
00:07:19.815 --> 00:07:21.191
Stop that boy!

117
00:07:21.275 --> 00:07:23.652
Hey! Stop him!

118
00:07:28.615 --> 00:07:29.700
Play! Play! Play!

119
00:07:29.783 --> 00:07:30.826
Play! Play! Play!
Play! Play!


120
00:07:30.909 --> 00:07:32.494
Play! Play! Play!

121
00:07:38.083 --> 00:07:39.376
Have you seen Cyrano?

122
00:07:39.459 --> 00:07:40.877
Not yet.

123
00:07:45.716 --> 00:07:48.260
Would you like an orange?
Yeah?


124
00:07:56.560 --> 00:07:59.855
Play! Play! Play!

125
00:07:59.938 --> 00:08:01.023
Theater.

126
00:08:01.106 --> 00:08:03.567
Inhale it, my boy.
Literally.


127
00:08:03.650 --> 00:08:05.277
Can you feel it? Yes?

128
00:08:05.360 --> 00:08:07.946
Tonight you will see
the magnificent Montfleury...


129
00:08:08.030 --> 00:08:10.449
the greatest actor
of his generation.


130
00:08:59.247 --> 00:09:00.540
Montfleury.

131
00:09:00.874 --> 00:09:01.875
Him?

132
00:09:07.172 --> 00:09:08.715
Montfleury!

133
00:09:08.799 --> 00:09:11.009
Bravo! Bravo!

134
00:09:15.389 --> 00:09:21.561
Happy is he who, far from court
and Society's sway...


135
00:09:21.645 --> 00:09:24.898
in isolation
self-imposed...


136
00:09:25.565 --> 00:09:27.192
shuns company.

137
00:09:27.276 --> 00:09:28.568
And who...

138
00:09:28.652 --> 00:09:32.656
when the soft wind
whistles wishingly...


139
00:09:32.739 --> 00:09:35.284
Montfleury, what are you
doing here?


140
00:09:35.367 --> 00:09:36.451
Cyrano?

141
00:09:36.535 --> 00:09:37.744
Cyrano?
Yes.


142
00:09:37.828 --> 00:09:39.746
After your performance
last week...


143
00:09:39.830 --> 00:09:43.292
I sent you a letter
urging you to retire.


144
00:09:43.375 --> 00:09:45.544
Cyrano.

145
00:09:45.627 --> 00:09:49.131
Happy is he who,
far from court and Society's...


146
00:09:49.214 --> 00:09:51.300
Did you receive my letter?

147
00:09:51.383 --> 00:09:54.845
Yes, I received
your letter, and I burnt it.


148
00:09:54.928 --> 00:09:57.556
I am
a professional actor.


149
00:09:57.639 --> 00:09:58.890
Yes, you are!
Bravo!


150
00:09:58.974 --> 00:10:00.684
I've received
numerous prizes.


151
00:10:00.767 --> 00:10:01.935
He has.

152
00:10:02.019 --> 00:10:04.605
I have performed at court
for the King himself.


153
00:10:04.688 --> 00:10:05.689
Indeed, you have.
Yes!


154
00:10:05.772 --> 00:10:07.482
Yes.

155
00:10:07.566 --> 00:10:11.778
I have been successfully
entertaining the people for over three decades.


156
00:10:13.322 --> 00:10:16.783
And now I will act!

157
00:10:16.867 --> 00:10:18.035
Act! Act! Act!
Act! Act! Act!


158
00:10:18.118 --> 00:10:19.494
Act! Act! Act!

159
00:10:19.578 --> 00:10:20.621
Act!

160
00:10:21.413 --> 00:10:23.123
Happy he who shuns...

161
00:10:23.206 --> 00:10:24.958
Final warning!

162
00:10:25.042 --> 00:10:28.253
In insulting me,
you insult the dramatic muse.


163
00:10:28.337 --> 00:10:32.424
And worse, you...
you desecrate this theater...


164
00:10:32.507 --> 00:10:36.053
this crucible
of human...


165
00:10:37.137 --> 00:10:38.430
humanity.

166
00:10:38.513 --> 00:10:39.598
Hear, hear!

167
00:10:39.681 --> 00:10:42.726
This sacred wooden O.

168
00:10:42.809 --> 00:10:45.729
No, sir. Untrue.

169
00:10:45.812 --> 00:10:48.231
I'm sorry, but you lie.

170
00:10:50.609 --> 00:10:53.528
You've made this stage
your personal sty!


171
00:10:53.612 --> 00:10:55.989
The dramatic muse
has fled the building.


172
00:10:56.073 --> 00:10:59.368
She scampered off when you
started gilding the lily...


173
00:10:59.451 --> 00:11:02.412
with your great big voice.

174
00:11:07.793 --> 00:11:10.462
The poor muse
had no choice.


175
00:11:11.546 --> 00:11:14.925
I love this place
and all it means.


176
00:11:15.008 --> 00:11:17.970
Poetry, romance,
terror, truth.


177
00:11:18.053 --> 00:11:21.139
I've loved it here
since early youth.


178
00:11:21.223 --> 00:11:23.558
Can't stand aside
while you dishonor it...


179
00:11:23.642 --> 00:11:26.228
with your pumping and
your hideous jigs.


180
00:11:26.311 --> 00:11:28.188
I will not abide
your thumping...


181
00:11:28.272 --> 00:11:31.024
and, er, dreadful wigs.

182
00:11:33.068 --> 00:11:35.028
Montfleury, you've
abandoned the truth.


183
00:11:35.112 --> 00:11:36.488
You've lost your core.

184
00:11:36.571 --> 00:11:39.199
You don't remember how truth
feels or what it's for.


185
00:11:39.283 --> 00:11:42.202
So, now leave this stage,
never to return.


186
00:11:42.286 --> 00:11:46.039
And I'll applaud the new
integrity you'll earn.


187
00:11:46.123 --> 00:11:48.500
Exit, Montfleury.

188
00:11:53.964 --> 00:11:56.675
I'm not moving one
step from the center of this stage.


189
00:11:56.758 --> 00:11:58.594
I am necessary.

190
00:11:58.677 --> 00:12:02.764
If you will not leave by
invitation, then I am compelled to use force.


191
00:12:04.766 --> 00:12:06.059
Help! Help me, someone!

192
00:12:06.143 --> 00:12:07.227
Protect me!

193
00:12:07.311 --> 00:12:08.770
Arrest him! Help!

194
00:12:08.854 --> 00:12:10.856
Please! Help me!

195
00:12:10.939 --> 00:12:14.026
-Please, Cyrano. Please. Will anyone here defend
-this great sausage?


196
00:12:17.362 --> 00:12:18.864
I will duel with any
volunteer...


197
00:12:18.947 --> 00:12:21.366
with all the honor commensurate
to his station.


198
00:12:21.450 --> 00:12:23.452
Is anyone
willing to fight for Montfleury?


199
00:12:23.535 --> 00:12:25.370
You are no Samson.

200
00:12:25.454 --> 00:12:28.624
I am no Goliath either, but I
fight like the two combined.


201
00:12:28.707 --> 00:12:29.875
I think not.

202
00:12:29.958 --> 00:12:32.169
Goliath was a giant.

203
00:12:32.252 --> 00:12:33.962
Care to think again?

204
00:12:35.130 --> 00:12:37.466
No volunteers?

205
00:12:37.549 --> 00:12:39.259
You came here to see
Montfleury...


206
00:12:39.343 --> 00:12:41.136
and yet you're
not willing to fight for him?


207
00:12:42.137 --> 00:12:43.764
Montfleury...
Sir, please.


208
00:12:43.847 --> 00:12:47.184
I will count to three, and you
will exit stage right hurriedly.


209
00:12:47.267 --> 00:12:48.352
Please.

210
00:12:48.435 --> 00:12:50.062
One...
Do something.


211
00:12:50.145 --> 00:12:52.272
Two...
Think of the play.


212
00:12:52.356 --> 00:12:53.649
Three!

213
00:12:56.526 --> 00:12:58.528
Ladies and gentlemen,
please.


214
00:13:08.205 --> 00:13:11.124
Jodelet!
I came to see a play!


215
00:13:11.208 --> 00:13:12.918
We paid
to see a play!


216
00:13:13.001 --> 00:13:16.088
And I have
saved you from seeing a fiasco!


217
00:13:16.171 --> 00:13:18.090
I paid
to see Montfleury!


218
00:13:18.173 --> 00:13:20.050
Yes, what
about their money?


219
00:13:20.133 --> 00:13:21.593
Always the money.

220
00:13:21.677 --> 00:13:22.678
Here.

221
00:13:25.389 --> 00:13:29.434
Oh, at this price, sir, you can
close the theaters every night.


222
00:13:29.518 --> 00:13:32.688
Ladies and gentlemen, you will
be refunded in full at the door.


223
00:13:32.771 --> 00:13:33.939
Dinner?

224
00:13:34.022 --> 00:13:36.400
Oh, I'd love to.
But no money.


225
00:13:36.483 --> 00:13:37.985
You had
a full bag of coins.


226
00:13:38.068 --> 00:13:40.696
All donated to the
long-suffering patrons of this theater.


227
00:13:40.779 --> 00:13:42.781
-How will you eat? The gesture is more
-than the meal.


228
00:13:42.864 --> 00:13:44.116
You.

229
00:13:45.784 --> 00:13:47.995
You're a freak.

230
00:13:49.746 --> 00:13:52.249
The insult is antique,
but I accept it.


231
00:13:54.710 --> 00:13:55.877
Freak.

232
00:13:57.796 --> 00:13:59.131
Is that it?

233
00:13:59.214 --> 00:14:01.967
Have you exhausted your
dictionary of scorn?


234
00:14:02.050 --> 00:14:04.803
Who is this savage who dares to
present himself in public...


235
00:14:04.886 --> 00:14:08.640
without ribbons,
bows or braids?


236
00:14:10.142 --> 00:14:11.977
I am not au courant,
it's true.


237
00:14:12.060 --> 00:14:15.897
But think of my deeds as my
ribbons, my humor as a bow.


238
00:14:15.981 --> 00:14:18.734
Oh, do pipe down,
or else you'll drown.


239
00:14:19.401 --> 00:14:20.736
In verbosity.

240
00:14:20.819 --> 00:14:22.904
A fellow poet.

241
00:14:22.988 --> 00:14:25.574
Pleasure to meet you.
Cyrano de Bergerac.


242
00:14:47.596 --> 00:14:49.848
I accept your challenge.

243
00:14:49.932 --> 00:14:52.225
I'll make
short work of this.


244
00:14:54.853 --> 00:14:56.688
Isn't he a hoot?

245
00:15:01.610 --> 00:15:03.028
A palpable miss.

246
00:15:03.111 --> 00:15:05.364
It's hard to
hit a target quite so small.


247
00:15:05.447 --> 00:15:07.491
The man is
barely four feet tall.


