<i>I lose myself every time</i>

486
00:29:27.517 --> 00:29:31.355
<i>Even now I'm overcome</i>

487
00:29:33.190 --> 00:29:39.488
<i>Roxanne, what am I</i>
<i>supposed to say?</i>


488
00:29:39.571 --> 00:29:44.576
<i>Words are only</i>
<i>glass on a string</i>


489
00:29:44.660 --> 00:29:47.454
<i>The more I arrange them</i>

490
00:29:47.537 --> 00:29:51.083
<i>And line up</i>
<i>and change them</i>


491
00:29:51.166 --> 00:29:55.003
<i>The more they mean</i>
<i>the same thing</i>


492
00:29:57.381 --> 00:29:58.924
<i>Roxanne</i>

493
00:30:00.300 --> 00:30:01.843
<i>Roxanne</i>

494
00:30:03.345 --> 00:30:05.180
<i>Roxanne</i>

495
00:30:09.184 --> 00:30:10.602
Roxanne!

496
00:30:10.686 --> 00:30:11.979
Roxanne.

497
00:30:19.695 --> 00:30:21.029
Do you like
rabbit stew?


498
00:30:21.113 --> 00:30:22.614
I loathe rabbits.

499
00:30:22.698 --> 00:30:24.783
I hate their taste, and I hate
the way they savage a garden.


500
00:30:24.866 --> 00:30:25.951
Shank of lamb?

501
00:30:26.034 --> 00:30:27.286
She likes tongue.

502
00:30:29.329 --> 00:30:31.623
For heaven's sake,
Marie.


503
00:30:31.707 --> 00:30:33.166
Go and eat.

504
00:30:33.250 --> 00:30:34.501
Fine.

505
00:30:34.584 --> 00:30:36.878
And I'll pray
for your sins while I do.


506
00:30:39.548 --> 00:30:41.675
A huge slab of tongue.
Keep it coming.


507
00:30:41.758 --> 00:30:43.051
Righto.

508
00:30:45.804 --> 00:30:48.765
I have a confession
to make.


509
00:30:51.560 --> 00:30:53.186
Shall we sit?

510
00:30:53.270 --> 00:30:54.354
You're wounded.

511
00:30:54.438 --> 00:30:55.439
A scratch.

512
00:30:56.565 --> 00:30:58.150
I know your shoddy work.

513
00:30:58.233 --> 00:31:00.360
The dressing is loose.

514
00:31:00.444 --> 00:31:01.695
Your confession?

515
00:31:01.778 --> 00:31:02.946
Can wait a moment.

516
00:31:03.030 --> 00:31:04.364
It's only a scratch.

517
00:31:04.448 --> 00:31:07.826
It's a wound,
and it needs cleaning.


518
00:31:07.909 --> 00:31:10.287
I've been wounded
many times.


519
00:31:10.370 --> 00:31:12.164
This is not a wound.

520
00:31:12.247 --> 00:31:14.333
Then we'll call it
a cut.


521
00:31:14.416 --> 00:31:15.667
"Scratch" is
more accurate.


522
00:31:15.751 --> 00:31:17.836
I dispute "more."

523
00:31:17.919 --> 00:31:20.088
A thing is either accurate
or it isn't.


524
00:31:21.632 --> 00:31:23.258
There are no degrees
of accuracy.


525
00:31:24.092 --> 00:31:25.677
You taught me that.

526
00:31:25.761 --> 00:31:27.137
As you wish.

527
00:31:27.220 --> 00:31:28.639
I'll settle
for "cut."


528
00:31:29.473 --> 00:31:31.266
A deep one.

529
00:31:35.312 --> 00:31:36.521
How did you get it?

530
00:31:36.605 --> 00:31:38.357
Last night.
A duel.


531
00:31:38.440 --> 00:31:39.566
And look what happens.

532
00:31:39.650 --> 00:31:41.026
You should see
the other guys.


533
00:31:41.109 --> 00:31:42.402
I'm not impressed
by your swordsmanship.


534
00:31:42.486 --> 00:31:43.654
Oh, I know.

535
00:31:43.737 --> 00:31:46.698
Or rather,
I know you pretend you're not.


536
00:31:46.782 --> 00:31:49.034
I'd be very angry with you
if you died.


537
00:31:49.117 --> 00:31:50.160
Only angry?

538
00:31:50.243 --> 00:31:51.787
Incandescent.

539
00:31:51.870 --> 00:31:53.205
This might hurt.

540
00:31:55.791 --> 00:31:57.042
So brave.

541
00:31:58.877 --> 00:32:00.712
Will you make
your confession?


542
00:32:00.796 --> 00:32:02.005
Yes, I must.

543
00:32:02.089 --> 00:32:04.675
And there's only so much tongue
Marie can chew on.


544
00:32:14.518 --> 00:32:16.061
I feel shy.

545
00:32:23.068 --> 00:32:24.236
Never mind.

546
00:32:27.823 --> 00:32:30.075
Yesterday,
at the theater...


547
00:32:30.158 --> 00:32:31.159
Yes?

548
00:32:32.160 --> 00:32:35.289
I can barely believe
I'm saying this.


549
00:32:35.372 --> 00:32:40.335
I realized,
or became aware, suddenly...


550
00:32:41.545 --> 00:32:43.088
that I was in love.

551
00:32:43.171 --> 00:32:44.548
I see.

552
00:32:44.631 --> 00:32:47.634
I am madly in love, but the man
in question has no idea.


553
00:32:47.718 --> 00:32:49.469
And I don't know
how to tell him.


554
00:32:49.553 --> 00:32:51.346
Perhaps he
feels the same?


555
00:32:51.430 --> 00:32:53.265
It's possible.
I have hopes.


556
00:32:53.348 --> 00:32:55.100
How do you know
you love him?


557
00:32:55.183 --> 00:32:57.477
Because it's as if
I've always known.


558
00:32:58.020 --> 00:32:59.771
Always known him.

559
00:32:59.855 --> 00:33:01.440
He was always there...

560
00:33:01.523 --> 00:33:03.233
but this intense romantic
connection had not yet manifested.


561
00:33:03.317 --> 00:33:05.402
I understand.

562
00:33:05.485 --> 00:33:06.778
Supposing it's
all a delusion?


563
00:33:06.862 --> 00:33:08.113
No, you're
clearly in love.


564
00:33:08.196 --> 00:33:09.489
My mind is racing.
I'm feverish.


565
00:33:09.573 --> 00:33:10.616
-Would you like some water?
-No.


566
00:33:10.699 --> 00:33:11.992
It's got your
blood in it.


567
00:33:12.075 --> 00:33:13.660
-You were saying? I don't know what
-I was saying.


568
00:33:13.744 --> 00:33:15.954
Tell me about him. It might
reassure you there's no delusion.


569
00:33:16.038 --> 00:33:17.122
Yes.

570
00:33:18.206 --> 00:33:19.207
Good.

571
00:33:21.084 --> 00:33:24.212
I feel
he is rather proud.


572
00:33:29.051 --> 00:33:31.136
And very charming.

573
00:33:31.219 --> 00:33:35.515
He is mysterious,
but not obscure.


574
00:33:35.599 --> 00:33:38.977
And his face
is so bright with intelligence.


575
00:33:39.061 --> 00:33:40.062
What else?

576
00:33:42.689 --> 00:33:45.150
He's very beautiful,
obviously.


577
00:33:45.233 --> 00:33:46.902
Is he?

578
00:33:46.985 --> 00:33:49.655
Yes. But his natural modesty
means he's completely unaware of it.


579
00:33:49.738 --> 00:33:51.073
I've met people
like that.


580
00:33:51.156 --> 00:33:52.324
They are so rare.
Yes.


581
00:33:52.407 --> 00:33:54.284
Perhaps I could make
a confession, too?


582
00:33:54.368 --> 00:33:55.702
Yes, but I haven't
made mine yet.


583
00:33:55.786 --> 00:33:57.287
I'm sorry.
Please continue.


584
00:33:57.371 --> 00:33:58.622
This man I love
is a guard.


585
00:33:58.705 --> 00:33:59.790
In your regiment.

586
00:33:59.873 --> 00:34:01.291
Of course he is.
Of course?


587
00:34:01.375 --> 00:34:02.459
In the sense that...

588
00:34:02.542 --> 00:34:05.170
I interrupted.
Please continue.


589
00:34:05.253 --> 00:34:09.007
It's embarrassing to admit, but
I've never actually spoken to him.


590
00:34:09.091 --> 00:34:11.551
Of your love?
Of anything.


591
00:34:11.635 --> 00:34:13.011
It was
love at first sight.


592
00:34:13.095 --> 00:34:14.721
A thunderbolt.
It's madness.


593
00:34:14.805 --> 00:34:15.889
Fantastical.

594
00:34:15.973 --> 00:34:18.642
And yet
it's absolutely...


595
00:34:19.935 --> 00:34:20.936
real.

596
00:34:30.737 --> 00:34:31.905
Cyrano?
Here.


597
00:34:31.989 --> 00:34:34.116
-You seem... Just the wound
-playing up.


598
00:34:35.158 --> 00:34:36.285
Poor you.

599
00:34:37.452 --> 00:34:39.121
I have some ointment
at home.


600
00:34:44.459 --> 00:34:48.755
Supposing he's
an idiot.


601
00:34:48.839 --> 00:34:52.551
He might just be
an incredibly beautiful man...


602
00:34:52.634 --> 00:34:54.303
with the mind
of a rabbit.


603
00:34:57.139 --> 00:34:58.140
Except he isn't.

604
00:35:00.183 --> 00:35:01.643
He can't be.

605
00:35:02.644 --> 00:35:04.229
I need him
not to be.


606
00:35:08.483 --> 00:35:12.529
Anyway, I've made
some discreet inquiries...


607
00:35:12.613 --> 00:35:15.073
and I am told that
he is Christian.


608
00:35:15.157 --> 00:35:16.241
Christian Neuvillette.

609
00:35:16.325 --> 00:35:18.243
"Neuvillette"?
Never heard of him.


610
00:35:18.327 --> 00:35:20.037
He's a new recruit.

611
00:35:20.662 --> 00:35:22.039
He starts today.

612
00:35:26.501 --> 00:35:27.794
To the point.

613
00:35:29.046 --> 00:35:30.505
To your presence
here...


614
00:35:32.883 --> 00:35:35.135
I know how the guards treat
the new recruits...


615
00:35:35.218 --> 00:35:37.971
your ancient
initiation rituals and so on.


616
00:35:38.055 --> 00:35:40.265
So, please,
will you protect him?


617
00:35:40.349 --> 00:35:42.100
I can refuse you nothing.

618
00:35:42.184 --> 00:35:43.560
And never let him
fight a duel?


619
00:35:43.644 --> 00:35:44.728
No.

620
00:35:44.811 --> 00:35:46.104
And guard his life
with your own?


621
00:35:46.188 --> 00:35:47.272
Yes.

622
00:35:47.356 --> 00:35:48.815
And be his friend?

623
00:35:48.899 --> 00:35:50.692
I might not like him.

624
00:35:50.776 --> 00:35:53.153
All the same.
Befriend him.


625
00:35:53.236 --> 00:35:54.279
Yes.

626
00:35:54.363 --> 00:35:56.073
And make him
write to me.


627
00:35:56.823 --> 00:35:58.575
And I'll write back.

628
00:35:58.659 --> 00:36:01.161
We'll exchange long,
poetic love letters.


629
00:36:01.244 --> 00:36:02.621
I will suggest that
he write to you...


630
00:36:02.704 --> 00:36:05.457
but I cannot control the content
or length of his letters.


631
00:36:08.043 --> 00:36:09.711
You are always so kind.

632
00:36:16.718 --> 00:36:17.719
No.

633
00:36:19.805 --> 00:36:22.266
You said you have a confession
to make, too.


634
00:36:24.226 --> 00:36:25.727
It's not important.

635
00:36:25.811 --> 00:36:27.396
I will support you
as you've supported me.


636
00:36:27.479 --> 00:36:29.106
Really, it's nothing.

637
00:36:31.275 --> 00:36:32.651
How's the hand?

638
00:36:32.734 --> 00:36:33.819
Painless.

639
00:36:33.902 --> 00:36:35.487
A scratch.

640
00:36:35.570 --> 00:36:37.823
How many men
did you duel with last night?


641
00:36:37.906 --> 00:36:39.199
A hundred.

642
00:36:39.283 --> 00:36:40.575
Really?

643
00:36:40.951 --> 00:36:42.286
Ten.

644
00:36:44.496 --> 00:36:47.040
All the same,
what courage.


645
00:36:50.585 --> 00:36:52.254
I've done better since.

646
00:36:55.757 --> 00:36:58.218
And one, two, three.

647
00:36:58.302 --> 00:37:01.513
One, two, three.
One, two, three.


648
00:37:01.597 --> 00:37:04.683
One, two, three.
One, two, three.


649
00:37:04.766 --> 00:37:07.769
One, two, three.
One, two, three.


650
00:37:07.853 --> 00:37:10.856
One, two, three.
One, two, three.


651
00:37:10.939 --> 00:37:12.691
One, two, three.

652
00:37:12.774 --> 00:37:16.236
And one, two. One, two.

653
00:37:16.320 --> 00:37:18.614
One, two. One, two.

654
00:37:18.697 --> 00:37:21.199
One, two. One, two.

655
00:37:21.283 --> 00:37:23.076
One, two, three.

656
00:37:23.994 --> 00:37:25.454
Captain.

657
00:37:27.289 --> 00:37:30.459
I heard of your recent
adventures.


658
00:37:30.542 --> 00:37:33.211
I've come to express
my admiration.


659
00:37:33.295 --> 00:37:34.338
Cyrano.

660
00:37:37.341 --> 00:37:40.552
I'm inviting you
to join my retinue.


661
00:37:40.636 --> 00:37:45.140
I thank the Duke for his
generous offer, but I must decline.


662
00:37:45.891 --> 00:37:47.559
Carry on!

663
00:37:47.643 --> 00:37:50.103
There are a great many
advantages to following me.


664
00:37:50.187 --> 00:37:51.271
I know.

665
00:37:51.355 --> 00:37:54.733
But I follow no one.

666
00:37:54.816 --> 00:37:59.112
I'm told that you write poetry
in common with a great many men these days.


667
00:37:59.196 --> 00:38:02.741
However, I'm told that you write
poetry uncommonly well.


668
00:38:02.824 --> 00:38:05.452
I like to publish those
that I admire.


669
00:38:05.535 --> 00:38:08.080
I could put you into print,
distinguish you.


670
00:38:08.163 --> 00:38:10.457
I'd only change a few lines.
I pay handsomely.


671
00:38:10.540 --> 00:38:13.752
You could buy a fine pair of
calfskin gloves.


672
00:38:13.835 --> 00:38:15.587
I'm not for sale.
Neither is my work.


673
00:38:15.671 --> 00:38:17.589
Aren't you proud.
Aren't you observant.


674
00:38:17.673 --> 00:38:19.591
Take this seriously.

675
00:38:19.675 --> 00:38:21.677
Those men last night
were incompetent.


676
00:38:21.760 --> 00:38:23.387
Others may not be.

677
00:38:25.222 --> 00:38:26.765
Someone's taken
against you.


678
00:38:26.848 --> 00:38:29.935
Join my retinue,
you'll be protected.


679
00:38:30.018 --> 00:38:32.437
First, you try to recruit me,
then you try to buy me.


680
00:38:32.521 --> 00:38:34.690
When you learn
I have no price...


681
00:38:34.773 --> 00:38:38.235
you warn me that my life is
threatened by an unknown enemy.


682
00:38:38.318 --> 00:38:39.861
I saw you last night.

683
00:38:39.945 --> 00:38:41.905
The blood of those men
is on your hands.


684
00:38:41.989 --> 00:38:44.283
You're a tyrant
posing as a noble.


685
00:38:44.366 --> 00:38:46.785
Oh, what a shame
we can't accommodate each other.


686
00:38:46.868 --> 00:38:48.453
'Cause you know something?

687
00:38:48.537 --> 00:38:51.164
You'd make a sweet little
companion to the acquisition I will make.


688
00:38:51.581 --> 00:38:52.791
Roxanne.

689
00:38:54.751 --> 00:38:55.961
Guards!

690
00:38:58.880 --> 00:39:00.090
<i>Don't push him too far.</i>

691
00:39:00.173 --> 00:39:02.551
To be his enemy
is a badge of honor.


692
00:39:02.634 --> 00:39:03.927
Which might
get you killed.


693
00:39:04.011 --> 00:39:05.095
Let him try.

694
00:39:05.178 --> 00:39:07.055
I'll best any he sends.

695
00:39:07.139 --> 00:39:08.181
Let them come.

696
00:39:08.265 --> 00:39:09.641
He offered you
a good wage.


697
00:39:09.725 --> 00:39:10.809
I belong here.

698
00:39:10.892 --> 00:39:12.978
With you. With them.

699
00:39:13.061 --> 00:39:16.064
Left! Left! Left! Right! Left!

700
00:39:16.148 --> 00:39:18.650
<i>I will not be his toy.</i>

701
00:39:18.734 --> 00:39:20.569
What would you
have me do, Le Bret?


702
00:39:21.403 --> 00:39:22.988
Join his retinue?

703
00:39:23.071 --> 00:39:24.156
No, thank you.

704
00:39:24.239 --> 00:39:26.825
<i>Dedicate poems</i>
<i>to de Guiche?</i>


705
00:39:26.908 --> 00:39:28.076
<i>No, thank you.</i>

706
00:39:35.626 --> 00:39:36.918
I've heard
how this works.


707
00:39:38.920 --> 00:39:39.921
Who's first?

708
00:39:44.927 --> 00:39:47.304
Do you want me
to swallow insults?


709
00:39:47.387 --> 00:39:49.681
To crawl? To kneel?
To beg?


710
00:39:49.765 --> 00:39:51.767
Play both sides?
Flatter? No, thank you.


711
00:39:53.644 --> 00:39:56.188
<i>Live for other people's</i>
<i>opinions of me?</i>


712
00:39:56.271 --> 00:39:59.191
No, thank you. I prefer a
different life. My own.


713
00:39:59.274 --> 00:40:02.027
I answer to no one,
and I am content, thank you.


714
00:40:04.488 --> 00:40:05.614
She doesn't love you?

715
00:40:07.491 --> 00:40:08.575
Don't...

716
00:40:08.659 --> 00:40:09.952
ever say it.

717
00:40:11.954 --> 00:40:13.664
Who's next?

718
00:40:15.791 --> 00:40:16.792
I am.

719
00:40:17.459 --> 00:40:18.460
Cyrano!

720
00:40:21.672 --> 00:40:25.759
Cyrano! Cyrano! Cyrano!

721
00:40:27.594 --> 00:40:29.221
What's so funny?

722
00:40:29.304 --> 00:40:32.224
First, I fight an elephant, and
now a mole?


723
00:40:33.433 --> 00:40:35.143
What's your name?

724
00:40:35.227 --> 00:40:36.436
Why?

725
00:40:36.520 --> 00:40:39.690
I just like to know
the names of the men I kill.


726
00:40:42.317 --> 00:40:44.987
I'm Christian Neuvillette, sir.

727
00:40:47.864 --> 00:40:49.157
Embrace me.

728
00:40:51.535 --> 00:40:52.703
Sir!

729
00:40:56.081 --> 00:40:57.332
I'm her brother.

730
00:41:06.300 --> 00:41:07.384
Whose brother?

731
00:41:07.467 --> 00:41:08.844
Who do you think?

732
00:41:08.927 --> 00:41:10.053
Roxanne.
Roxanne?


733
00:41:10.137 --> 00:41:11.179
Hmm.

734
00:41:13.181 --> 00:41:14.474
Yes.

735
00:41:14.558 --> 00:41:15.851
You don't look
like her brother.


736
00:41:15.934 --> 00:41:17.936
We're old friends,
like siblings but not.


737
00:41:18.020 --> 00:41:19.104
We're very close.

738
00:41:19.187 --> 00:41:20.439
And what...
She's told me everything.


739
00:41:20.522 --> 00:41:22.274
The theater,
love at first sight, all of it.


740
00:41:22.357 --> 00:41:23.567
She loves me?

741
00:41:23.650 --> 00:41:25.027
She believes so.

742
00:41:25.110 --> 00:41:26.570
Sir, I am so glad
to know you!


743
00:41:26.653 --> 00:41:27.904
Yes, enough of that.

744
00:41:27.988 --> 00:41:29.281
-Please forgive me for insulting you earlier.
-Yes.


745
00:41:29.364 --> 00:41:30.365
I just...
Yes, yes.


746
00:41:30.449 --> 00:41:32.284
She loves me!
Now, listen.


747
00:41:32.367 --> 00:41:33.744
She loves me!

748
00:41:33.827 --> 00:41:35.495
Roxanne wants
a letter from you.


749
00:41:36.747 --> 00:41:37.789
No?
Impossible.


750
00:41:37.873 --> 00:41:38.957
If I write to her,
it'll drive her away.


751
00:41:39.041 --> 00:41:40.125
Really? Why?

752
00:41:40.208 --> 00:41:41.209
