01:27:12.524 --> 01:27:14.276
<i>Form line!</i>

1448
01:27:17.070 --> 01:27:19.364
This child has delivered our
orders from the King.


1449
01:27:23.702 --> 01:27:24.828
These are from de Guiche.

1450
01:27:24.911 --> 01:27:26.872
Correct.
In service of the King.


1451
01:27:28.290 --> 01:27:30.250
We've been holding this
godforsaken rock for months.


1452
01:27:30.334 --> 01:27:32.044
On the King's orders.

1453
01:27:32.127 --> 01:27:35.005
And now we have the noble
distinction of being chosen to mount an attack.


1454
01:27:36.632 --> 01:27:37.925
De Guiche wants me dead.

1455
01:27:38.008 --> 01:27:39.718
The odds are against us.

1456
01:27:42.804 --> 01:27:45.390
I'd rather die down there
fighting...


1457
01:27:45.474 --> 01:27:47.017
than starve up here waiting.

1458
01:27:48.936 --> 01:27:50.270
Then ready yourself.

1459
01:27:55.108 --> 01:27:56.526
Form line!

1460
01:27:59.112 --> 01:28:00.989
Captain, steady your men!

1461
01:28:01.907 --> 01:28:03.992
Collect the letters.

1462
01:28:13.669 --> 01:28:16.046
<i>I have a wife</i>

1463
01:28:16.129 --> 01:28:18.674
<i>I haven't seen</i>

1464
01:28:18.757 --> 01:28:21.969
<i>Since lilacs bloomed</i>
<i>in Saint-Hippolyte</i>


1465
01:28:23.553 --> 01:28:25.389
<i>She always wears them</i>

1466
01:28:26.306 --> 01:28:28.517
<i>In her hair</i>

1467
01:28:28.600 --> 01:28:32.604
<i>And she lets them fall down</i>
<i>everywhere</i>


1468
01:28:32.688 --> 01:28:38.068
<i>I can see her</i>
<i>in the glowing light</i>


1469
01:28:38.151 --> 01:28:41.488
<i>Dressing without a sound</i>

1470
01:28:42.990 --> 01:28:47.244
<i>I promised</i>
<i>I'd be home all right</i>


1471
01:28:47.327 --> 01:28:51.873
<i>But I gotta</i>
<i>lay this body down</i>


1472
01:28:53.709 --> 01:28:56.253
<i>So take this letter</i>

1473
01:28:56.336 --> 01:28:58.630
<i>To my wife</i>

1474
01:28:58.714 --> 01:29:01.800
<i>And tell her that</i>
<i>I loved my life</i>


1475
01:29:03.802 --> 01:29:05.929
<i>And tell my boys</i>

1476
01:29:06.013 --> 01:29:08.640
<i>The Lord, he found me</i>

1477
01:29:08.724 --> 01:29:10.892
<i>When I say</i>
<i>their names out loud</i>


1478
01:29:10.976 --> 01:29:12.894
<i>They're all around me</i>

1479
01:29:12.978 --> 01:29:14.187
<i>And tell 'em</i>

1480
01:29:16.440 --> 01:29:20.277
<i>Not to cry at all</i>

1481
01:29:23.363 --> 01:29:26.283
<i>Heaven</i>

1482
01:29:26.366 --> 01:29:30.621
<i>Is wherever I fall</i>

1483
01:29:33.624 --> 01:29:36.126
<i>I have a girl</i>

1484
01:29:36.209 --> 01:29:37.794
<i>I think I love her</i>

1485
01:29:38.837 --> 01:29:40.589
<i>I should have told her</i>

1486
01:29:40.672 --> 01:29:42.591
<i>Instead I told her mother</i>

1487
01:29:43.759 --> 01:29:46.303
<i>I gave her chocolates</i>

1488
01:29:46.386 --> 01:29:47.554
<i>I bought a ring</i>

1489
01:29:48.764 --> 01:29:52.684
<i>But I never told her</i>
<i>anything</i>


1490
01:29:52.768 --> 01:29:58.315
<i>But I can see her</i>
<i>in every detail now</i>


1491
01:29:58.398 --> 01:30:01.818
<i>Turning in my mind</i>

1492
01:30:03.236 --> 01:30:07.407
<i>I barely knew</i>
<i>that girl at all</i>


1493
01:30:07.491 --> 01:30:10.327
<i>But I will love her till</i>
<i>the end of time</i>


1494
01:30:13.789 --> 01:30:16.333
<i>So take this letter</i>

1495
01:30:16.416 --> 01:30:18.794
<i>To my girl</i>

1496
01:30:18.877 --> 01:30:23.507
<i>Tell her that I saw</i>
<i>the whole world</i>


1497
01:30:23.590 --> 01:30:28.178
<i>Say that right before I fell</i>

1498
01:30:28.262 --> 01:30:30.514
<i>I said her name out loud</i>

1499
01:30:31.682 --> 01:30:33.225
<i>Isabelle</i>

1500
01:30:33.308 --> 01:30:35.352
<i>And tell her</i>

1501
01:30:36.520 --> 01:30:39.982
<i>Not to cry at all</i>

1502
01:30:43.527 --> 01:30:46.530
<i>Heaven</i>

1503
01:30:46.613 --> 01:30:50.284
<i>Is wherever I fall</i>

1504
01:30:53.829 --> 01:30:55.455
<i>I have a father</i>

1505
01:30:56.373 --> 01:30:57.541
<i>He isn't well</i>

1506
01:30:59.001 --> 01:31:02.462
<i>He thinks he might be</i>
<i>going to hell</i>


1507
01:31:03.922 --> 01:31:05.424
<i>He was a sinner</i>

1508
01:31:06.300 --> 01:31:07.718
<i>He liked to fight</i>

1509
01:31:09.094 --> 01:31:12.848
<i>So I don't know</i>
<i>he might be right</i>


1510
01:31:12.931 --> 01:31:18.228
<i>I can see him</i>
<i>every Sunday morning</i>


1511
01:31:18.312 --> 01:31:21.857
<i>Diving into the fray</i>

1512
01:31:23.275 --> 01:31:28.030
<i>He wasn't</i>
<i>one of God's best men</i>


1513
01:31:28.113 --> 01:31:32.200
<i>But I loved him anyway</i>

1514
01:31:33.910 --> 01:31:35.329
<i>So take this letter</i>

1515
01:31:36.663 --> 01:31:39.124
<i>To him, please</i>

1516
01:31:39.207 --> 01:31:42.669
<i>And tell him I can't wait</i>
<i>to see him</i>


1517
01:31:43.962 --> 01:31:45.339
<i>I went in first</i>

1518
01:31:46.465 --> 01:31:48.967
<i>I rang the bell</i>

1519
01:31:49.051 --> 01:31:52.763
<i>I called his name out loud</i>
<i>and I gave 'em hell</i>


1520
01:31:52.846 --> 01:31:54.514
<i>So tell him</i>

1521
01:31:56.683 --> 01:32:00.354
<i>Not to cry at all</i>

1522
01:32:03.607 --> 01:32:06.610
<i>Heaven</i>

1523
01:32:06.693 --> 01:32:10.155
<i>Is wherever I fall</i>

1524
01:32:13.408 --> 01:32:14.409
<i>Tell 'em</i>

1525
01:32:16.536 --> 01:32:20.791
<i>Not to cry at all</i>

1526
01:32:23.502 --> 01:32:26.463
<i>Heaven</i>

1527
01:32:26.546 --> 01:32:30.425
<i>Is wherever I fall</i>

1528
01:32:33.262 --> 01:32:34.346
<i>Tell 'em</i>

1529
01:32:34.429 --> 01:32:35.555
Roxanne.

1530
01:32:36.556 --> 01:32:39.351
<i>Not to cry at all</i>
I know.


1531
01:32:39.434 --> 01:32:41.436
I wish I could
write her one last letter.


1532
01:32:43.355 --> 01:32:45.649
You have.
<i>Heaven</i>


1533
01:32:45.732 --> 01:32:46.817
Let me see.

1534
01:32:46.900 --> 01:32:48.485
<i>Is wherever I fall</i>

1535
01:32:48.568 --> 01:32:50.195
No need.

1536
01:32:50.279 --> 01:32:51.822
Of course
there's a need.


1537
01:33:08.755 --> 01:33:10.215
What's this?

1538
01:33:10.299 --> 01:33:11.550
What?

1539
01:33:11.633 --> 01:33:13.302
This.

1540
01:33:13.385 --> 01:33:14.511
It's a tear stain.

1541
01:33:14.595 --> 01:33:16.221
Is it? That's odd.

1542
01:33:19.308 --> 01:33:23.103
We poets sometimes are so moved
by our own creations that we...


1543
01:33:23.186 --> 01:33:24.229
It's poetic empathy.

1544
01:33:25.606 --> 01:33:27.399
You cried
writing this letter?


1545
01:33:30.027 --> 01:33:33.030
Yes. I cannot
bear not to see her again.


1546
01:33:35.574 --> 01:33:37.159
We will never
see her again.


1547
01:33:37.242 --> 01:33:41.246
You, her beloved husband, might
die and never see her again.


1548
01:33:41.330 --> 01:33:42.623
That is the tear stain.

1549
01:33:44.791 --> 01:33:46.084
You're in love
with her.


1550
01:33:46.168 --> 01:33:47.169
What?

1551
01:33:48.420 --> 01:33:50.505
You've gone mad.
You're starving.


1552
01:33:50.589 --> 01:33:52.132
Deny it then.

1553
01:33:53.508 --> 01:33:54.676
Do you love her?

1554
01:33:59.139 --> 01:34:00.515
It's too simple.

1555
01:34:03.894 --> 01:34:05.145
I knew it.

1556
01:34:06.521 --> 01:34:08.523
But I didn't...

1557
01:34:08.607 --> 01:34:10.609
I didn't dare
let myself believe it.


1558
01:34:11.652 --> 01:34:12.819
I feel sick.

1559
01:34:12.903 --> 01:34:14.738
You've always loved her.
I will deny it.


1560
01:34:14.821 --> 01:34:16.448
You can't deny it.
You can't even hide it.


1561
01:34:16.531 --> 01:34:18.158
Christian, listen to me.

1562
01:34:18.241 --> 01:34:20.160
If I should die and you should
live, and she mentions the letters...


1563
01:34:20.243 --> 01:34:21.912
do not be surprised...
At what?


1564
01:34:21.995 --> 01:34:23.747
If she mentions
their volume.


1565
01:34:23.830 --> 01:34:25.749
You've written to her
more often than you know.


1566
01:34:25.832 --> 01:34:27.834
How often?
Often enough.


1567
01:34:27.918 --> 01:34:29.544
Twice a week?
More.


1568
01:34:29.628 --> 01:34:31.296
Three times a week?
More than that.


1569
01:34:31.380 --> 01:34:33.131
Four? Five?
More.


1570
01:34:33.215 --> 01:34:34.675
Every day?
Yes, every day.


1571
01:35:03.578 --> 01:35:05.372
She doesn't love me.

1572
01:35:05.455 --> 01:35:07.791
Of course she does.

1573
01:35:07.874 --> 01:35:10.794
In her most recent letter,
she said she loves me...


1574
01:35:10.877 --> 01:35:12.212
because of my soul.

1575
01:35:13.130 --> 01:35:14.631
What could be
more loving?


1576
01:35:14.715 --> 01:35:16.258
You are my soul!

1577
01:35:21.972 --> 01:35:23.348
We have to
tell her the truth...


1578
01:35:24.516 --> 01:35:26.685
and you must
confess your love.


1579
01:35:26.768 --> 01:35:28.979
The world will never
accept a midget...


1580
01:35:29.062 --> 01:35:30.981
and a tall
beautiful woman.


1581
01:35:31.064 --> 01:35:33.525
Never mind the world.
What about Roxanne?


1582
01:35:34.985 --> 01:35:37.696
She's got a huge heart.

1583
01:35:37.779 --> 01:35:41.700
In the same letter, she
reassured me that she'd still love me...


1584
01:35:41.783 --> 01:35:44.995
even if I return
from this hell a broken man...


1585
01:35:45.078 --> 01:35:47.205
disfigured and
body destroyed.


1586
01:35:47.289 --> 01:35:48.540
She said that?

1587
01:36:05.515 --> 01:36:06.558
Don't believe her.

1588
01:36:06.642 --> 01:36:07.893
Don't doubt her.

1589
01:36:09.353 --> 01:36:11.563
Take your positions!

1590
01:36:14.191 --> 01:36:15.400
We have betrayed her.

1591
01:36:15.484 --> 01:36:17.194
We can never tell her.
It'll break her heart.


1592
01:36:17.277 --> 01:36:18.570
We have to tell her.

1593
01:36:18.654 --> 01:36:20.405
It's our moral...

1594
01:36:20.489 --> 01:36:21.657
Our moral...

1595
01:36:22.950 --> 01:36:24.576
Obligation.

1596
01:36:24.660 --> 01:36:25.744
See you on the other side!

1597
01:36:25.827 --> 01:36:27.746
We must let her
decide our fate.


1598
01:36:27.829 --> 01:36:30.666
One of us,
none of us...


1599
01:36:30.749 --> 01:36:32.584
She must have
the choice.


1600
01:36:32.668 --> 01:36:34.294
Form the line!

1601
01:36:36.505 --> 01:36:39.216
And I'm certain
she'll choose you.


1602
01:36:39.299 --> 01:36:40.676
She's already
chosen you.


1603
01:36:40.759 --> 01:36:42.511
Love at first sight.
She married you.


1604
01:36:42.594 --> 01:36:44.221
She doesn't love me.
She doesn't even know me.


1605
01:36:44.304 --> 01:36:45.681
She doesn't
love me either.


1606
01:36:45.764 --> 01:36:47.683
I think she does.

1607
01:36:47.766 --> 01:36:50.686
And I would prefer to be loved
for my true self or not at all.


1608
01:36:52.688 --> 01:36:54.147
Get ready!

1609
01:36:54.940 --> 01:36:56.066
Christian.

1610
01:36:56.149 --> 01:36:57.859
Attention!

1611
01:36:57.943 --> 01:36:59.236
<i>Tell 'em</i>

1612
01:36:59.319 --> 01:37:01.071
See you on the other side!

1613
01:37:01.154 --> 01:37:05.033
<i>Not to cry at all</i>

1614
01:37:08.245 --> 01:37:10.330
<i>Heaven</i>

1615
01:37:11.164 --> 01:37:15.502
<i>Is wherever I fall</i>

1616
01:37:15.585 --> 01:37:18.046
Soldier, back in line!

1617
01:37:18.130 --> 01:37:19.631
<i>Tell 'em</i>

1618
01:37:19.715 --> 01:37:21.091
Soldier!

1619
01:37:21.174 --> 01:37:25.596
<i>Not to cry at all</i>
Christian! No!


1620
01:37:28.181 --> 01:37:30.809
<i>Heaven</i>

1621
01:37:30.892 --> 01:37:35.814
<i>Is wherever I fall</i>

1622
01:38:08.555 --> 01:38:10.015
You will live.

1623
01:38:12.017 --> 01:38:16.647
You will live for Roxanne
who loves you.


1624
01:38:21.026 --> 01:38:23.570
Tell her everything.

1625
01:38:23.654 --> 01:38:24.655
Please.

1626
01:38:26.657 --> 01:38:27.866
Everything.

1627
01:38:32.788 --> 01:38:34.289
Roxanne.

1628
01:38:39.503 --> 01:38:40.879
Forward!

1629
01:38:40.963 --> 01:38:44.508
Forward! Forward! Forward!

1630
01:38:51.056 --> 01:38:52.266
<i>Tell 'em</i>

1631
01:38:54.142 --> 01:38:58.355
<i>Not to cry at all</i>

1632
01:39:01.149 --> 01:39:04.278
<i>Heaven</i>

1633
01:39:04.361 --> 01:39:08.615
<i>Is wherever I fall</i>

1634
01:39:10.701 --> 01:39:12.077
<i>Tell 'em</i>

1635
01:39:13.912 --> 01:39:18.166
<i>Not to cry at all</i>

1636
01:39:19.334 --> 01:39:23.797
Make ready! And fire!
<i>Heaven</i>


1637
01:39:23.880 --> 01:39:27.926
<i>Is wherever I fall</i>

1638
01:39:30.095 --> 01:39:31.430
Fire!
<i>Tell 'em</i>


1639
01:39:33.557 --> 01:39:37.769
<i>Not to cry at all</i>

1640
01:39:37.853 --> 01:39:39.104
Fire!

1641
01:39:40.355 --> 01:39:43.483
<i>Heaven</i>

1642
01:39:43.567 --> 01:39:48.488
<i>Is wherever I fall</i>

1643
01:39:56.121 --> 01:40:00.959
Sister Claire, must I remind
you, you have accepted a life without mirrors?


1644
01:40:01.043 --> 01:40:02.628
Stop admiring yourself...

1645
01:40:02.711 --> 01:40:04.463
or I will be forced
to tell Cyrano.


1646
01:40:04.546 --> 01:40:06.757
Oh, no.
He'll make such fun of me.


1647
01:40:06.840 --> 01:40:10.469
And promise me you will stop
trying to convert him.


1648
01:40:10.552 --> 01:40:13.764
He's been coming here every
Saturday for as long as I can remember.


1649
01:40:14.598 --> 01:40:16.516
Why does he
not believe?


1650
01:40:16.600 --> 01:40:18.477
Miss Roxanne
is his faith.


1651
01:40:18.560 --> 01:40:21.063
His weekly visits
are his service.


1652
01:40:21.146 --> 01:40:23.482
It saddens me
he won't see heaven.


1653
01:40:23.565 --> 01:40:26.151
I'm sure the Lord
has a plan for him.


1654
01:40:26.234 --> 01:40:28.862
You should worry about
his remaining time on Earth.


1655
01:40:28.946 --> 01:40:30.656
Get him to eat.

1656
01:40:30.739 --> 01:40:32.991
He always says
he's not hungry.


1657
01:40:33.075 --> 01:40:35.243
He says,
"I ate good meat yesterday."


1658
01:40:35.327 --> 01:40:37.079
It's not true.

1659
01:40:37.162 --> 01:40:39.706
He's too proud
to admit he can't afford it.


1660
01:40:39.790 --> 01:40:41.333
He's starving.

1661
01:40:41.416 --> 01:40:43.335
Insist he eats with us
this evening.


1662
01:40:43.418 --> 01:40:44.836
Yes, Mother.

1663
01:40:44.920 --> 01:40:46.964
He'll be here at six o'clock to
bring her the news.


1664
01:40:50.801 --> 01:40:51.843
<i>Dear Roxanne...</i>

1665
01:40:51.927 --> 01:40:53.720
<i>Dear Roxanne.</i>

1666
01:40:53.804 --> 01:40:56.181
<i>...how many times have I</i>
<i>sat by your side and wanted to tell you?</i>


1667
01:40:56.265 --> 01:40:57.307
<i>Dear Roxanne.</i>

1668
01:40:57.391 --> 01:40:58.392
<i>Almost told you?</i>

1669
01:40:58.475 --> 01:40:59.643
<i>Dear Roxanne.</i>

1670
01:40:59.726 --> 01:41:01.353
<i>There is nothing</i>
<i>so dangerous and sweet...</i>


1671
01:41:01.436 --> 01:41:03.105
<i>to keep as</i>
<i>a secret like this.</i>


1672
01:41:03.188 --> 01:41:05.274
<i>I have sublimated.</i>

1673
01:41:05.357 --> 01:41:06.900
<i>Tell her. Tell her.</i>

1674
01:41:06.984 --> 01:41:08.527
<i>How many letters</i>
<i>have I written...</i>


1675
01:41:08.610 --> 01:41:09.653
<i>Tell her.</i>

1676
01:41:09.736 --> 01:41:10.737
<i>Trying to spell it out plainly.</i>

1677
01:41:10.821 --> 01:41:11.905
Plainly.

1678
01:41:11.989 --> 01:41:13.198
<i>Simply.</i>

1679
01:41:14.116 --> 01:41:15.158
Simply.

1680
01:41:17.744 --> 01:41:19.204
Without art.

1681
01:41:22.124 --> 01:41:23.125
Ob...

1682
01:41:42.477 --> 01:41:44.146
<i>Tell her the truth.</i>

1683
01:41:44.229 --> 01:41:46.398
<i>You. Always you.</i>

1684
01:41:46.481 --> 01:41:47.733
<i>You. You.</i>

1685
01:41:47.816 --> 01:41:49.735
<i>I love you.</i>
<i>I've always loved you.</i>


1686
01:41:49.818 --> 01:41:51.695
<i>Tell her. Tell her.</i>

1687
01:41:51.778 --> 01:41:54.489
<i>I will die loving you,</i>
<i>and you will never know.</i>


1688
01:41:54.573 --> 01:41:55.991
<i>Tell her.</i>

1689
01:42:41.912 --> 01:42:43.538
He'll be here.

1690
01:42:43.622 --> 01:42:45.624
He's always on time.

1691
01:42:48.710 --> 01:42:50.420
Going somewhere?

1692
01:42:53.048 --> 01:42:54.132
You're late.

1693
01:42:54.216 --> 01:42:55.717
I was delayed.

1694
01:42:56.718 --> 01:42:57.803
By what?

1695
01:42:57.886 --> 01:42:59.429
An untimely visitor.

1696
01:43:03.642 --> 01:43:05.102
You sent him away?

1697
01:43:07.396 --> 01:43:12.025
I fear I only
put him off for a short while.


1698
01:43:12.109 --> 01:43:14.152
Well, he will
have to wait...


1699
01:43:14.236 --> 01:43:17.781
because I will not
let you leave before nightfall.


1700
01:43:17.864 --> 01:43:19.116
You've cut yourself.

1701
01:43:20.575 --> 01:43:22.911
A scratch, really.

1702
01:43:25.831 --> 01:43:28.000
Aren't you going to
tease Sister Claire?


1703
01:43:28.083 --> 01:43:30.210
She waits for it
all week, you know.


1704
01:43:32.129 --> 01:43:34.214
Sister Claire,
you have such lovely eyes.


1705
01:43:34.298 --> 01:43:36.049
Why do you keep them
cast down?


1706
01:43:37.217 --> 01:43:39.303
I ate good meat
yesterday.


1707
01:43:40.679 --> 01:43:42.764
When you're ready,
come to the dining hall.


1708
01:43:42.848 --> 01:43:44.433
Then I'll give you
a big bowl of soup.


1709
01:43:44.516 --> 01:43:46.059
Yes.
Good.


1710
01:43:46.143 --> 01:43:48.770
I think Sister Claire
is trying to convert you.


1711
01:43:48.854 --> 01:43:49.855
I am not.

1712
01:43:50.522 --> 01:43:51.857
Mother warned me off.

1713
01:43:55.110 --> 01:43:56.111
Sister Claire.

1714
01:43:57.696 --> 01:44:00.449
Tonight, I will let you
pray for me.


1715
01:44:02.618 --> 01:44:04.911
I have not waited
for your permission.


1716
01:44:16.798 --> 01:44:18.967
Do you remember
the day we first met?


1717
01:44:22.471 --> 01:44:23.555
Yes.

1718
01:44:25.641 --> 01:44:27.935
It was early morning
in early June.


1719
01:44:29.353 --> 01:44:32.064
I'd come to borrow a book
from your father.


1720
01:44:32.147 --> 01:44:37.569
We found you curled up on the
floor in the library in the dawn light...


1721
01:44:37.653 --> 01:44:40.739
a tome for a pillow.

1722
01:44:40.822 --> 01:44:43.742
You were reading
the very book that I'd come for.


1723
01:44:45.160 --> 01:44:46.453
I refused to give it up.

1724
01:44:48.330 --> 01:44:50.457
Your youth
made it forgivable.


1725
01:44:50.540 --> 01:44:52.209
I hadn't finished
reading it.


1726
01:44:52.292 --> 01:44:53.919
I didn't mind.

1727
01:44:54.002 --> 01:44:55.837
You said you'd give it to me
when you had.


1728
01:44:55.921 --> 01:44:57.172
And I did.

1729
01:44:59.841 --> 01:45:02.386
It was as if
we'd always known each other.


1730
01:45:04.179 --> 01:45:05.847
And now we have.

1731
01:45:09.476 --> 01:45:13.438
They say light
is the soul of a holy space.


1732
01:45:13.522 --> 01:45:15.399
It's designed
to be enough.


1733
01:45:17.693 --> 01:45:19.194
Enough beauty...

1734
01:45:22.864 --> 01:45:24.574
to just let go.

1735
01:45:30.038 --> 01:45:31.498
Are you melancholy?

1736
01:45:33.125 --> 01:45:34.167
No.

1737
01:45:34.251 --> 01:45:35.419
No.

1738
01:45:43.051 --> 01:45:44.803
Do you have
my daily paper?


1739
01:45:44.886 --> 01:45:46.179
Yes, I do.

1740
01:45:46.263 --> 01:45:47.389
Good.

1741
01:45:50.434 --> 01:45:53.478
Last Saturday, the 19th,
I saw you.


1742
01:45:53.562 --> 01:45:55.897
And then a week passed in which
nothing important happened...


1743
01:45:55.981 --> 01:45:57.065
and now here
I am again.


1744
01:45:57.149 --> 01:45:58.900
Cyrano.
All right.


1745
01:45:59.818 --> 01:46:01.403
The news.

1746
01:46:11.663 --> 01:46:15.375
On Saturday, the head of state
ate too many prunes...


1747
01:46:15.459 --> 01:46:17.669
and he took to his bed
with a fever.


1748
01:46:17.753 --> 01:46:20.172
He was executed by his
physician...


1749
01:46:20.255 --> 01:46:22.174
and now he is feeling
much better.


1750
01:46:25.093 --> 01:46:27.471
There was a ball
on Sunday...


1751
01:46:27.554 --> 01:46:32.476
and 762 wax candles
were burned...


1752
01:46:34.811 --> 01:46:35.812
out.

1753
01:46:38.857 --> 01:46:43.570
On Monday, our troops were
reported to have beaten everyone...


1754
01:46:43.654 --> 01:46:44.947
everywhere.

1755
01:46:47.240 --> 01:46:52.788
On Tuesday, a tiny little dog
had to be given a very large enema.


1756
01:47:00.671 --> 01:47:02.297
On Wednesday, nothing.

1757
01:47:04.299 --> 01:47:07.052
On Thursday...

1758
01:47:07.135 --> 01:47:11.223
someone somewhere,
who isn't us, took a new lover.


1759
01:47:15.769 --> 01:47:17.145
On Friday...

1760
01:47:18.981 --> 01:47:20.649
I was the queen...

1761
01:47:25.237 --> 01:47:26.488
of almost.

1762
01:47:31.076 --> 01:47:32.244
Today...

1763
01:47:37.332 --> 01:47:39.418
Today, I...

1764
01:47:39.501 --> 01:47:40.669
I...

1765
01:47:41.878 --> 01:47:43.255
I...

1766
01:47:51.722 --> 01:47:53.724
Shall we get you
that soup?


1767
01:47:57.853 --> 01:47:59.438
Not yet.

1768
01:47:59.521 --> 01:48:00.731
Not yet.

1769
01:48:01.565 --> 01:48:02.816
Oh, my dear.

1770
01:48:04.109 --> 01:48:05.569
What is to be done?

1771
01:48:07.112 --> 01:48:09.364
Just my old wound
from the war.


1772
01:48:10.949 --> 01:48:12.492
Damn that war.

1773
01:48:23.879 --> 01:48:27.382
You told me one day you would
let me read Christian's last letter.


1774
01:48:31.219 --> 01:48:32.304
Now?

1775
01:48:35.307 --> 01:48:36.308
Please.

1776
01:49:04.252 --> 01:49:05.504
Thank you.

1777
01:49:16.974 --> 01:49:19.351
"Farewell, Roxanne...

1778
01:49:19.434 --> 01:49:22.437
"I believe this will be
my last day, my beloved.


1779
01:49:23.772 --> 01:49:27.025
"My soul is heavy
with unexpressed love.


1780
01:49:28.610 --> 01:49:31.863
"Fullness of heart
cannot be recorded.


1781
01:49:31.947 --> 01:49:34.992
"It will not live on
in my bones when I am gone.


1782
01:49:37.369 --> 01:49:39.538
"It will not be buried
in my grave.


1783
01:49:40.998 --> 01:49:43.458
"The exact measure of my love
cannot be given to you...


1784
01:49:43.542 --> 01:49:45.585
"in words to outlast
my last breath.


1785
01:49:45.669 --> 01:49:47.879
"No matter how I wish it,
for I am dust.


1786
01:49:47.963 --> 01:49:49.631
"And dust to dust...

1787
01:49:50.799 --> 01:49:53.010
"I'm going to die today,
my love."


1788
01:49:53.093 --> 01:49:54.469
You are not reading.

1789
01:49:56.221 --> 01:49:57.848
You are remembering.

1790
01:50:05.856 --> 01:50:07.399
It was you.

1791
01:50:07.482 --> 01:50:08.567
No, Roxanne.

1792
01:50:08.650 --> 01:50:10.902
Make your confession.
No, Roxanne.


1793
01:50:10.986 --> 01:50:12.154
The letters.
No.


1794
01:50:12.237 --> 01:50:13.322
The words.
No.


1795
01:50:13.405 --> 01:50:15.407
The voice in the night
below my balcony.


1796
01:50:15.490 --> 01:50:17.034
All of it. You.

1797
01:50:17.117 --> 01:50:19.036
I married him that night
because of your words.


1798
01:50:19.119 --> 01:50:20.245
You married him,
not my words.


1799
01:50:20.329 --> 01:50:21.496
Why are you denying it?

1800
01:50:21.580 --> 01:50:23.582
Because I do not love you,
my love.


1801
01:50:24.708 --> 01:50:26.668
Yes, you do.
Christian loved you.


1802
01:50:26.752 --> 01:50:28.420
You wrote that letter.
No.


1803
01:50:28.503 --> 01:50:30.172
That tear is yours.
The blood is his!


1804
01:50:30.255 --> 01:50:32.799
Why tell me now? Why?

1805
01:50:32.883 --> 01:50:35.093
I believe this will be
my last day.


1806
01:50:35.177 --> 01:50:36.178
No.

1807
01:50:39.681 --> 01:50:40.766
No.

1808
01:50:42.017 --> 01:50:43.060
No.

1809
01:50:45.270 --> 01:50:47.773
<i>No, Cyrano</i>

1810
01:50:47.856 --> 01:50:50.984
<i>I won't let you go</i>

1811
01:50:51.068 --> 01:50:55.238
<i>How can you not see?</i>

1812
01:50:56.531 --> 01:50:59.451
<i>I'm alone, Cyrano</i>

1813
01:50:59.534 --> 01:51:02.955
<i>I've nowhere to go</i>

1814
01:51:03.038 --> 01:51:07.459
<i>You have to stay with me</i>

1815
01:51:09.419 --> 01:51:11.463
<i>Oh, Roxanne</i>

1816
01:51:11.546 --> 01:51:14.841
<i>I don't understand</i>

1817
01:51:14.925 --> 01:51:19.304
<i>The one you love's not here</i>

1818
01:51:20.847 --> 01:51:23.308
<i>I buried that man</i>

1819
01:51:23.392 --> 01:51:26.395
<i>With my very own hands</i>

1820
01:51:26.478 --> 01:51:31.233
<i>Long ago</i>
<i>in a blackberry field</i>


1821
01:51:32.651 --> 01:51:37.572
- <i>Have you ever wanted</i>
-<i>something</i>


1822
01:51:38.740 --> 01:51:44.246
